At first this game is quite fun. The mechanics are simple and easy to 
understand. But instead of expanding on the base mechanics the levels just 
become increasingly precise. You'll know what you have to do after the 
first try, but it could take you 100 to actually get the timing right. It 
gets to the point where completing a level feels like a stroke of luck 
rather than something you had control over which gets very frustrating very 
fast. the graphics are pleasing and the concept is interesting, but the 
gameplay falls short.
